<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-07-03T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-07-03T05:00:00-05:00" n="188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b W 52/141: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-03T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 3,
                                        1923—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 12:51
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>264. Your 165, June 30, 2 p.m. The second paragraph of the offer
                            mentioned relates to all traffic originating in South Europe, i.e., the
                            south to be served by the Italian cable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi></signed></closer>
